ons/bottletr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why people leave EQ</span><hr size=1> Ahhh the real reason!! as compared to all the unreal ones right? which are?? ....never mind....<br>
<br>
State the obvious please! someone may have missed it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
it would be expedient for myself for example to say, &quot;its not fun anymore therefore I quit&quot; however thats really not the point of the thread is it? to be utterly expedient, otherwise I would have reduced my post for example to a single full stop &quot;.&quot;   Utterly expressing stopping and yet saying absolutely nothing at all. A little more texture than that would be interesting dont you think?<br>
<br>
By all means have your say on the topic but save the claims of divine knowledge of the &quot;only real reason&quot; for a more gullible readership. Its pretty rich really considering you still play, eg havent quit and therefore have no personal experience of quitting motivation.<br>
<br>
Like someone who has never awoken the sleeper speaking with feigned authority on the subject.<br>
<br>
Now on one level I agree with you, if it isnt &quot;fun&quot; people quit. But &quot;fun&quot; is a pretty broad term isnt it, lots of different meaning to lots of different people. But just saying<br>
 (no fun=quit)<br>
reduces the matter to a meaningless formula. You may as well just use my full stop from above. Reduction to absurdity.<br>
